The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Aug. 29 (PTI): Over 50 lakh government employees, including the armed forces personnel, will receive an enhanced pay packet from September 1, with the government today notifying the revised recommendations of the Sixth Pay Commission.          
	The commission proposals had been approved by the Union cabinet a fortnight ago after it amended certain recommendations of the Justice Sri Krishna-led pay commission.                  
	 New Delhi: Foreign minister Pranab Mukherjee on Friday said Delhi was working with the Nuclear Suppliers Group to secure a clean waiver on its guidelines. We have made our position quite clear to the interlocutors, Mukherjee told reporters. India is trying to narrow down differences with some NSG countries, including Austria, New Zealand, Switzerland and Ireland, before their next NSG meeting.                  
	 Melbourne (PTI): Australian police on Friday dropped the case involving Indian doctor Mohammed Haneef, wrongly accused of involvement in the failed UK car bombings last year, because of insufficient evidence.                  
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): Twelve schoolchildren were injured on Friday when the bus in which they were travelling collided with a tree. The driver had lost control while ferrying the children to school.                  
	 Vellore (PTI): One person has been arrested for trying to sneak ganja into the Vellore central prison, police said on Friday. Officials said the 28-year-old-man had come to the prison on the pretext of visiting a relative. When police checked his bag they found a coconut. They broke it open to find 75 grams of ganja.                   
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A man was sentenced to life imprisonment by a local court on Friday for murdering his brother over a property dispute here. The district session judge also slapped a fine of Rs 5,000 on Ahsan, 26.                                                                                                                          
